Ask HN: Stripe dashboard fails to display- could a Stripe dev help?
text:
Hi HN,

Resorting to the good ol' "expose-problems-on-the-frontpage-of-HN-to-get-a-solution" hack since Stripe support basically told me that it's not their problem and that I should contact Firefox.

Here's the deal: my Stripe dashboard won't load (Error: Unable to load this view) across multiple pages (home page, payments, connect and more...) and I've been unable to view my stats for several (non-consecutive) days now. It works on Chrome but not on Firefox and I really don't want to have to switch to Chrome to access a website made by a multi-billion company counting hundreds of engineers.

I'm using Firefox@latest on MacOS 10.14 (Mojave). I opened up the browser console and found several warnings (related to cookies apparently) and at least one failed GET request: https://imgur.com/a/6No50sP

When I clear my cache / cookies and log back in, it usually fixes the problem for about 30min.

Could any dev @ Stripe chime in?

Appreciate your help!

Show HN: Evaluate Deep Learning models directly in a database with PyNeuraLogic
text:
Hi HN. PyNeuraLogic is a Python Deep Relational Learning framework. With the latest release of PyNeuraLogic, we have introduced a set of tools for working with databases as a data source and, most notably, a tool to transpile deep learning models to (Postgres) SQL.

We have prepared a short tutorial on those tools (link in the banner in the README).

Let us know if you have any feedback or questions regarding the framework!

Ask HN: When will earth hit peak population? And what do you think it will be?
text:
Hi HN,

This question popped up in my head recently, when Elon Musk made the conjecture that declining growth rate of population in the west (& everywhere) is the biggest threat to humanity.

Rising costs and evolving gender roles is causing people to reproduce less and later than usual. This phenomenon seems inevitable pretty much everywhere.

If this peak point is closer than expected, this could have big implications on the maximum size a organization could have.

Will the world have many trillion dollar companies if the population is not 7 billion anymore?

Maybe we live in one of the only few hundred year window where growth prospects are large enough for such large valuations to be sustainable.

What do you think?
